@startuml State_PlaidItem
title Plaid Item State Machine

skinparam state {
    BackgroundColor<<success>> LightGreen
    BackgroundColor<<warning>> LightYellow
    BackgroundColor<<error>> LightCoral
    BackgroundColor<<terminal>> LightGray
}

[*] --> Pending : User initiates\nPlaid Link

Pending --> Active <<success>> : Public token\nexchanged successfully
Pending --> Error <<error>> : Token exchange\nfails

Active --> Active : Transaction sync\ncompletes successfully
Active --> NeedsReauth <<warning>> : PENDING_EXPIRATION\nwebhook received
Active --> Error <<error>> : ITEM_ERROR\nwebhook received
Active --> Disconnected <<terminal>> : User disconnects\nor revokes access

NeedsReauth --> Active <<success>> : User completes\nLink update flow
NeedsReauth --> Error <<error>> : Re-auth window\nexpires
NeedsReauth --> Disconnected <<terminal>> : User disconnects

Error --> Active <<success>> : Issue resolved via\nLink update flow
Error --> Disconnected <<terminal>> : User disconnects\nor max retries exceeded

Disconnected --> [*]

note right of Active
  Normal operating state.
  Transaction sync runs
  on webhook trigger and
  daily fallback schedule.
end note

note right of NeedsReauth
  Plaid credentials expiring.
  User must re-authenticate
  via Link update mode.
  Sync continues with
  existing credentials.
end note

note right of Error
  Plaid reports an error
  (e.g., ITEM_LOGIN_REQUIRED).
  Sync is paused until
  the user re-authenticates.
end note

@enduml
